A section of fence is shown below.  What is the length of the gap between each post?

\begin{center}
\includegraphics[scale=0.3]{images/ds_l1.png}
\end{center}
}

\textbf{Answer:} Since the total length is 192 cm and the three posts have a combined length of $16\cdot 3$ cm, the two gaps have a combined length of 144 cm.  Dividing by 2, we find that each gap is $\boxed{72}$ cm.
